subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. 

Arenigena floridensis

is similar to 

A. albiseta

and 

A. semitaria

in the male having the inner gonocoxal process bilobed (
Fig. 74
). It differs from 

A. albiseta

in having the gonocoxite ventral view (
Fig. 73
) lacking a posteromedial aggregation of dense setae; the ventral lobe (
Fig.73
) with apical setae; the dorsal apodeme (
Fig. 76
) moderately expanded laterally with the anterior margin emarginate; and the furca (
Fig. 79
) quadrate with the posterior margin truncate. It differs from 

A. semitaria

in having wing veins and cross-veins yellow, lacking a brown margin; the proepimeron setose across the dorsal margin; the male sternite 8 with setae continuous across posterior margin (
Fig. 73
); the ventral lobe (
Fig.73
) with apical setae; the dorsal apodeme (
Fig. 76
) broadly rounded laterally with the anterior margin emarginate; and the furca (
Fig. 79
) quadrate with the posterior margin truncate.

Abdomen.
Pubescence white, dense; dorsal setae white, elongate, erect, abundant; lateral setae white, elongate. 

Terminalia

(MEI 128599) brown. Tergite 8 (
Fig. 72
), setae pale yellow. Sternite 8 (
Fig. 73
), rectangular, sides rounded, posterior margin truncate; setae pale yellow, continuous across posterior margin. Epandrium (
Fig. 72
) quadrate; posterolateral margin short, broadly pointed; setae yellow. Cerci (
Fig. 72
), ending basal to apex of hypoproct. Hypoproct (
Fig. 72
), posterior margin deeply emarginate. Gonocoxite ventral view (
Fig. 73
), quadrate, median margin tapering posteriorly to blunt point, setae yellow; lateral view (
Fig. 74
), oval, tapering posteriorly to blunt point, inner gonocoxal process bilobed, dorsal projection broadly pointed with dark yellow apical setae, ventral projection narrow; ventral lobe (
Fig. 73
) with short setae apically. Gonostylus lateral view (
Fig. 75
) thick, cylindrical, broadly curved posterodorsally; setae yellow. Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme (
Fig. 76
) broad, expanded posterolaterally, anterior margin emarginate; ventral apodeme (
Fig. 77
), broad, sides parallel, anterior margin truncate; distiphallus dorsal view (
Fig.76
) broad basally, tapered posteriorly; lateral view (
Fig. 78
) thick basally, sinuate; aedeagal apodeme (
Figs. 76–77
) extending beyond anterior margin of dorsal apodeme.
